---
title: "About — Slade Networks"
description: "Slade Networks designs and installs UniFi network infrastructure for businesses and homes across the Finger Lakes, NY. Learn about our standards, approach, and founder."
navActive: about
---
{% extends "base.njk" %}

{% block pageStyles %}
  <style>
    .aboutGrid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 20px;
      align-items: stretch;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .aboutCard {
      background: var(--white);
      border: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
      border-radius: var(--r-xl);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
      padding: 28px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .aboutCard h2 {
      margin: 0 0 10px;
      font-size: 20px;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }

    .aboutCard p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--gray-600);
      font-size: 14.5px;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }
    .aboutCard p + p { margin-top: 12px; }

    /* Founder card */
    .founderHeader {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 16px;
      margin-top: 14px;
    }

    .headshot {
      width: 72px;
      height: 72px;
      border-radius: var(--r-lg);
      overflow: hidden;
      border: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
      background: var(--gray-50);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }

    .headshot img {
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover;
      display: block;
    }

    .founderBio {
      margin-top: 16px;
      color: var(--gray-600);
      font-size: 14px;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }
    .founderBio + .founderBio { margin-top: 10px; }

    .pillRow {
      margin-top: 16px;
      display: flex;
      gap: 10px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .pill {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
      padding: 8px 14px;
      border-radius: var(--r-full);
      border: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
      background: var(--gray-50);
      color: var(--gray-600);
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: 500;
      line-height: 1;
      white-space: nowrap;
      transition: border-color .2s var(--ease), background .2s var(--ease);
    }
    .pill:hover {
      border-color: var(--primary-200);
      background: var(--primary-50);
      color: var(--primary);
    }

    /* Standards cards */
    .standardsGrid {
      margin-top: 18px;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 14px;
      flex: 1;
      align-content: start;
    }

    .standardCard {
      padding: 16px 18px;
      border-radius: var(--r-lg);
      border: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
      background: var(--gray-50);
    }

    .standardCard h3 {
      margin: 0 0 6px;
      font-size: 14.5px;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--gray-900);
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }

    .standardCard p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--gray-600);
      font-size: 13.5px;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    /* Divider between sections */
    .aboutDivider {
      border: none;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
      margin: 32px 0;
    }

    /* Process teaser strip */
    .processBanner {
      background: var(--white);
      border: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
      border-radius: var(--r-xl);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
      padding: 24px 28px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 20px;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .processBanner p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--gray-600);
      font-size: 14.5px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      max-width: 56ch;
    }

    .processBanner strong {
      display: block;
      font-size: 16px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--gray-900);
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin-bottom: 4px;
    }

    .hero { padding-bottom: 40px; }
    .aboutSection { padding: 24px 0 0; }
    .ctaSection { padding: 24px 0 72px; }

    @media(max-width: 980px) {
      .aboutGrid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .processBanner { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
    }

    @media(max-width: 700px) {
      .aboutSection { padding: 32px 0 0; }
    }
  </style>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <main>

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="heroBadge">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
          Finger Lakes, NY
        </div>
        <h1>Professional Networks.<br>Personal Accountability.</h1>
        <p class="subtext">
          Slade Networks designs, installs, and supports network infrastructure for businesses and homes across the Finger Lakes — using commercial-grade equipment, a consistent process, and a standard that holds long after the install is done.
        </p>
        <div class="heroButtons">
          <a class="btn primary" href="/contact/">Get a free consultation</a>
          <a class="btn" href="/process/">See how a project works</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Founder + Standards -->
    <section class="aboutSection">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="aboutGrid reveal-stagger">

          <!-- Founder -->
          <div class="aboutCard">
            <h2>Andrew Slade</h2>
            <div class="founderHeader">
              <div class="headshot">
                <img src="/assets/Headshot.jpg" alt="Andrew Slade, founder of Slade Networks" loading="lazy">
              </div>
              <p style="margin:0; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:-0.01em; color:var(--gray-900); font-size:14px;">Founder</p>
            </div>
            <p class="founderBio">
              Andrew founded Slade Networks after seeing too many businesses and homes in the Finger Lakes stuck with unreliable networks and no qualified local option to turn to.
            </p>
            <p class="founderBio">
              He graduated from St. Bonaventure University with a degree in Computer Science and holds a Cisco CCNA certification. His focus has always been practical, real-world networking — the kind that performs on day 300 the same way it did on day one.
            </p>
            <div class="pillRow" aria-label="Credentials">
              <span class="pill">B.S. Computer Science — St. Bonaventure University</span>
              <span class="pill">Cisco CCNA</span>
              <span class="pill">UniFi specialist</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Standards -->
          <div class="aboutCard">
            <h2>What every project is held to</h2>
            <p>These aren't aspirational — they're the baseline for every job, from a single access point to a full commercial install.</p>

            <div class="standardsGrid reveal-stagger">
              <div class="standardCard">
                <h3>Commercial gear, sourced direct</h3>
                <p>Equipment is purchased straight from Ubiquiti — no gray-market hardware, no inflated reseller pricing. You get the same commercial-grade UniFi gear used in enterprise deployments.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="standardCard">
                <h3>Written quote before any work begins</h3>
                <p>A detailed plan and fixed cost upfront. No scope changes happen without your approval, and no surprise line items appear on the final invoice.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="standardCard">
                <h3>Full admin access is yours, always</h3>
                <p>Your network belongs to you. Every project is documented, labeled, and handed off with complete admin credentials — no ongoing dependency on Slade Networks to make changes.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Process teaser -->
        <div class="processBanner reveal">
          <div>
            <strong>Not sure what to expect?</strong>
            <p>Every project follows the same clear process — free on-site visit, written quote, clean install, and a full walkthrough before we leave. No obligation at any step.</p>
          </div>
          <a class="btn" href="/process/" style="flex-shrink:0;">See the process</a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="ctaSection reveal">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="ctaInner">
          <div>
            <h2>Ready to talk about your network?</h2>
            <p>Describe what you're dealing with and you'll get a clear response — no sales pitch, just honest next steps.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ctaButtons">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/contact/">Start a conversation</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
{% endblock %}
